1
00:00:04,713 --> 00:00:06,881
<i>The serial murders happening recently…</i>

2
00:00:06,965 --> 00:00:08,883
<i>They are similar to the Shiramine case.</i>

3
00:00:08,967 --> 00:00:11,428
Could you please
tell me what happened back then?

4
00:00:11,511 --> 00:00:13,263
Stop making a fool out of me.

5
00:00:13,346 --> 00:00:15,181
Mizusawa Masumi, was it?

6
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:16,891
<i>He is a bit of an eyesore, isn't he?</i>

7
00:00:16,975 --> 00:00:19,811
MEJ will be shut down
by the end of this month.

8
00:00:25,358 --> 00:00:26,317
What?

9
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:27,569
Shut down?

10
00:00:28,361 --> 00:00:29,612
Why so suddenly?

11
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:32,198
Is there a reason for this?

12
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:35,785
I haven't been told the details either.

13
00:00:36,786 --> 00:00:37,746
However,

14
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:40,915
the MEJ was originally
an experimental operation,

15
00:00:41,416 --> 00:00:43,960
and the higher-ups said
they already have enough data

16
00:00:44,043 --> 00:00:47,672
to debate whether to officially
implement it.

17
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:50,967
Even so, this is far too sudden.

18
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:53,428
What are we supposed to do now?

19
00:00:57,348 --> 00:01:00,602
What you are all saying
is completely justified.

20
00:01:01,644 --> 00:01:04,439
I am truly sorry for my lack of skill.

21
00:01:04,939 --> 00:01:07,358
It's not your fault, Ms. Kiryu.

22
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:12,072
Dr. Masumi,
you don't agree with this either, right?

23
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:15,366
Dr. Masumi,

24
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:16,993
I'm sorry.

25
00:01:20,705 --> 00:01:25,460
If only I had done a better job promoting
the significance of the MEJ…

26
00:01:25,543 --> 00:01:27,045
Ms. Kiryu,

27
00:01:28,046 --> 00:01:29,339
you are not to blame.

28
00:01:31,382 --> 00:01:32,634
It's my responsibility.

29
00:01:44,562 --> 00:01:46,189
-Hello.
-Good work.

30
00:01:52,362 --> 00:01:53,196
Hello.

31
00:01:53,279 --> 00:01:54,114
Hello.

32
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:57,242
Yukie Morishita, 23 years old.

33
00:01:57,325 --> 00:02:00,537
After she'd called her father
last night around 9 p.m.,

34
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:02,247
she became unreachable.

35
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:04,958
A passerby discovered the body
this morning.

36
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:07,585
Another strangulation of a young woman…

37
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:10,130
It has finally happened
in our jurisdiction too.

38
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:11,714
This makes six victims already.

39
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:16,761
It really is similar.

40
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:17,846
What?

41
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:21,891
Well, I'll contact the MEJ.

42
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,687
Oh, they're gone now, right? Sorry.

43
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:36,030
I'll leave it to you.

44
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:40,994
Ms. Kiryu, here.

45
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:42,245
Please review this.

46
00:02:43,454 --> 00:02:44,622
Oh, okay.

47
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:50,044
Are you still thinking about the MEJ?

48
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:52,672
Oh, yes.

49
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:56,301
It's not your fault.

50
00:02:56,968 --> 00:03:01,514
In the first place, Japan isn't ready
for the MEJ system itself.

51
00:03:03,808 --> 00:03:06,769
All the staff members
managed to find new workplaces, right?

52
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:11,649
I heard that you found them their jobs.

53
00:03:12,525 --> 00:03:16,321
I somehow managed to find positions
for all the young doctors.

54
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:19,365
Then you've got nothing to worry about.

55
00:03:28,374 --> 00:03:32,211
Your mother
was trying to protect someone else,

56
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,047
and got into an accident.

57
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,803
That is not something just anyone can do.

58
00:03:41,804 --> 00:03:43,348
She was an incredible person.

59
00:03:45,016 --> 00:03:46,684
How do you know?

60
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:50,104
I know by listening to their voices.

61
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:53,107
But people can't talk once they're dead.

62
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:54,776
That's true.

63
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:56,778
But…

64
00:03:57,946 --> 00:03:59,739
I can listen to them.

65
00:04:12,001 --> 00:04:13,002
Come in.

66
00:04:14,003 --> 00:04:15,171
Excuse me.

67
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:19,509
Masumi?

68
00:04:23,721 --> 00:04:25,014
The other day,

69
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:29,269
I went to meet Shinichi Serizawa
at the detention center.

70
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:36,651
I asked him if he would tell me
what happened back then once more,

71
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:39,445
but he refused.

72
00:04:40,905 --> 00:04:42,031
I see.

73
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:44,534
And,

74
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:51,082
the MEJ was suddenly shut down.

75
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:57,005
On the surface,
it was a notice from the MHLW,

76
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:58,756
but maybe,

77
00:04:59,757 --> 00:05:02,719
it's a warning from the prosecution

78
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:06,806
not to dig any deeper
into the Shiramine case.

79
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:11,602
It's one thing if it's just me,

80
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:16,399
but taking away the workplace
of young forensic pathologists

81
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:20,528
is something I can't ever accept.

82
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:25,533
I believe we cannot back down now,
for the sake of Serizawa,

83
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:28,369
who maintains his innocence.

84
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:32,749
I will ask you once more.

85
00:05:34,542 --> 00:05:36,085
What on earth

86
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:38,296
happened back then?

87
00:05:42,842 --> 00:05:43,926
Professor,

88
00:05:44,802 --> 00:05:46,846
please tell me the truth!

89
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:57,023
There are people
who have been suffering for 15 years.

90
00:05:57,106 --> 00:06:00,318
Besides, we cannot allow any more victims.

91
00:06:01,569 --> 00:06:05,448
What is it that you are trying
to protect, Professor?

92
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:10,995
Listening to the final voices
of the deceased…

93
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:15,792
The person who taught me
how to face someone's loved one

94
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,586
was you, Professor.

95
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,888
I…

96
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:34,894
will not give up again.

97
00:06:49,325 --> 00:06:52,453
I believe in you, Professor.

98
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,066
Yukie?

99
00:07:25,987 --> 00:07:26,821
Yukie?

100
00:07:29,031 --> 00:07:30,908
Why? Why?!

101
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:32,535
Yukie!

102
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:36,247
Yukie!

103
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:38,916
Why…

104
00:07:41,919 --> 00:07:43,087
Yukie…

105
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:50,470
Mr. Morishita.

106
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:55,683
We will now have to perform

107
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:59,353
a judicial autopsy on Yukie's body.

108
00:08:00,396 --> 00:08:01,355
Autopsy?

109
00:08:02,773 --> 00:08:04,984
It is to investigate
Yukie's cause of death

110
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:07,695
and find traces
that might lead to the perpetrator.

111
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:09,155
Don't!

112
00:08:11,866 --> 00:08:14,911
Yukie has already gone through
something so terrible.

113
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:21,042
Please don't hurt my daughter any more.

114
00:08:21,709 --> 00:08:23,586
I understand how you feel.

115
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:25,421
However,

116
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:32,345
a judicial autopsy cannot be stopped
by the wishes of the bereaved family.

117
00:08:35,014 --> 00:08:36,432
I am truly sorry.

118
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:48,736
<i>Moving on to the next story,</i>

119
00:08:48,819 --> 00:08:53,491
<i>this morning, the body of a young woman</i>
<i>was discovered on a street in Tokyo.</i>

120
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:55,576
<i>According to investigative sources,</i>

121
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:58,329
<i>authorities are proceeding</i>
<i>under the belief</i>

122
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:00,790
<i>that this is connected</i>
<i>to the serial murders.</i>

123
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:04,752
<i>As of now, no definitive eyewitness</i>
<i>information has been obtained…</i>

124
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:10,007
Hello!

125
00:09:10,716 --> 00:09:15,012
No eyewitnesses and not a trace
that might lead to the killer.

126
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:17,431
-You can't enter here!
-Please let me through.

127
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:19,517
No unauthorized personnel may enter.

128
00:09:20,851 --> 00:09:21,936
Please.

129
00:09:22,019 --> 00:09:24,146
-The investigation is--
-Isn't that Dr. Masumi?

130
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:25,398
Why is he here?

131
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:27,233
Let me explain again.

132
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:28,484
Doctor.

133
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:29,735
What are you doing?

134
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:31,571
Ms. Dojima, I'm glad you're here.

135
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:34,740
Could you please
let me investigate the case as well?

136
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:36,576
I can't do that.

137
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:37,994
What?

138
00:09:38,077 --> 00:09:41,872
No one except those involved
in the investigation can enter here.

139
00:09:41,956 --> 00:09:44,125
You aren't involved anymore, right?

140
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:47,086
Could you at least let me see the body?

141
00:09:47,169 --> 00:09:50,423
The body is already
on its way to the autopsy.

142
00:09:51,048 --> 00:09:52,466
Please leave.

143
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:56,929
This serial murder case might be connected
to an incident from the past!

144
00:09:57,013 --> 00:10:00,641
There's no way that's true!
Don't make up things to try to get in.

145
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:01,726
Right?

146
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:06,439
Tell me more.

147
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:26,917
Are you Yukie Morishita's father?

148
00:10:28,544 --> 00:10:29,420
Yes.

149
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:33,424
My name is Kyoko Kujo. I'm a pathologist.

150
00:10:34,425 --> 00:10:36,802
I will be performing
the autopsy on your daughter.

151
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:39,263
Doctor…

152
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:44,185
Do you really have to do the autopsy?

153
00:10:46,687 --> 00:10:50,983
I can't bear for my daughter's body
to be hurt any more than it has.

154
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:55,446
I really do understand how you feel.

155
00:10:57,782 --> 00:10:59,116
After work…

156
00:11:00,868 --> 00:11:02,953
I should have just taken her home.

157
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:06,582
Because of me, Yukie…

158
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:08,584
It is not your fault.

159
00:11:09,251 --> 00:11:12,588
The one at fault is the criminal
who took your daughter's life.

160
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:17,009
To get justice for your daughter,

161
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:20,596
please allow me to investigate this.

162
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:32,316
Please take care of my daughter.

163
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:52,670
SHIRAMINE SERIAL FEMICIDE CASE

164
00:11:52,753 --> 00:11:54,004
I knew it.

165
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:57,216
This is about
the Shiramine case, isn't it?

166
00:11:58,008 --> 00:11:59,635
-Yes.
-Huh?

167
00:11:59,718 --> 00:12:01,971
What is the Shiramine case?

168
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:03,597
It was a series of murders

169
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:08,185
that took place in West Tokyo,
in Shiramine, 15 years ago.

170
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:12,356
<i>The three victims</i>
<i>were all females in their twenties,</i>

171
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:15,025
<i>and the cause of death</i>
<i>was always strangulation</i>

172
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:17,778
<i>by something like a belt.</i>

173
00:12:18,362 --> 00:12:19,780
<i>Shinichi Serizawa,</i>

174
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:23,534
<i>who worked at the same place</i>
<i>as one of the victims, was arrested.</i>

175
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:25,161
<i>He was found guilty</i>

176
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:28,289
<i>and his death penalty</i>
<i>was finalized because of DNA evidence</i>

177
00:12:28,372 --> 00:12:31,500
<i>and lack of an alibi</i>
<i>at the estimated time of death.</i>

178
00:12:32,751 --> 00:12:35,296
Strangling young women…

179
00:12:35,379 --> 00:12:38,507
It's just like the serial killings
happening right now.

180
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:41,051
I was considering that maybe

181
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:44,638
this is the work of a copycat criminal
imitating the Shiramine case.

182
00:12:44,722 --> 00:12:45,681
A copycat?

183
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,726
I…

184
00:12:49,518 --> 00:12:51,020
don't think so.

185
00:12:52,688 --> 00:12:54,482
I don't suspect a copycat.

186
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:57,526
I suspect the possibility
of a repeat offense.

187
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:58,903
A repeat offense?

188
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:00,488
On what grounds?

189
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:03,866
But you just said the culprit
was already caught, didn't you?

190
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:08,704
The forensic examiner
in charge of the Shiramine case

191
00:13:09,371 --> 00:13:12,082
was my mentor, Professor Kujo.

192
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:17,254
<i>I also participated in the autopsy</i>
<i>as an assistant.</i>

193
00:13:18,714 --> 00:13:21,467
However, those forensic findings

194
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:25,721
differed from the facts.

195
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:28,224
What do you mean?

196
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:29,975
During the autopsy,

197
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:34,772
skin fragments believed to belong
to the killer were found on the body,

198
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:39,527
but there wasn't a sufficient amount
to perform a DNA test.

199
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:41,862
And yet,

200
00:13:42,738 --> 00:13:45,866
the forensic report
he submitted to the prosecution

201
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:50,037
<i>stated that it matched</i>
<i>Serizawa's DNA profile.</i>

202
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:53,707
So that doctor
fabricated the forensic results

203
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:58,504
just to frame
Shinichi Serizawa as the culprit?

204
00:13:59,171 --> 00:14:00,214
Most likely.

205
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:08,013
Professor Kujo

206
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:13,060
is the person who performed
the autopsy on my mother

207
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:16,105
after she died in an accident
when I was a child.

208
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:23,445
When I was frightened of my mother's body

209
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:27,116
<i>and was unable to face her death,</i>

210
00:14:29,076 --> 00:14:30,995
<i>he said it wasn't just a dead body.</i>

211
00:14:31,495 --> 00:14:36,584
He explained to me she was
a person who had loved,

212
00:14:37,626 --> 00:14:39,503
and was loved by others.

213
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:43,257
Those words

214
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:47,386
really saved me.

215
00:14:50,764 --> 00:14:52,141
For Professor Kujo

216
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:56,186
to fabricate forensic results…

217
00:14:57,605 --> 00:15:00,357
They must have put
an immense amount of pressure on him.

218
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:05,946
At the time,

219
00:15:06,822 --> 00:15:10,910
I realized the fabrication
and tried to blow the whistle on him,

220
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:12,161
but…

221
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:15,331
I was kicked out of the lab

222
00:15:16,165 --> 00:15:19,627
and couldn't gather enough evidence.

223
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:25,549
I knew that the autopsy I was involved in
had created a wrongful conviction.

224
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:31,013
I just couldn't accept that fact.

225
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,850
I fled Japan.

226
00:15:42,816 --> 00:15:44,777
If Serizawa is innocent,

227
00:15:46,737 --> 00:15:49,406
then the real culprit is still out there.

228
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:51,408
Does that mean that same killer

229
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:57,164
is now murdering people again?

230
00:15:57,247 --> 00:15:58,999
It's a possibility.

231
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,751
But it has been 15 years.

232
00:16:00,834 --> 00:16:02,419
Why would they start again now?

233
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:04,797
I don't know.

234
00:16:05,381 --> 00:16:07,341
-You're overthinking this.
-No…

235
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:10,344
It might actually make sense.

236
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:11,762
What?

237
00:16:12,262 --> 00:16:14,974
At the time, the investigation
was getting desperate

238
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:17,726
because they couldn't identify a suspect.

239
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:19,812
Then, eyewitness information on Serizawa

240
00:16:19,895 --> 00:16:22,982
surfaced at a suspiciously
convenient time.

241
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:26,402
Meaning they fabricated
the eyewitness testimony?

242
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:28,779
I thought it was just a rumor.

243
00:16:28,862 --> 00:16:30,948
But if it's true…

244
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:34,576
then the Shiramine case

245
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:39,498
is something the prosecution
would definitely want to keep buried.

246
00:16:39,581 --> 00:16:45,295
That's why when the prosecution found out
I met with Professor Kujo and Serizawa,

247
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:50,676
they pressured the Ministry
to force the closure of the MEJ.

248
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:53,804
All to cover up their past blunder.

249
00:16:53,887 --> 00:16:57,099
Ms. Dojima, it's better
if you don't dig any deeper into this.

250
00:16:57,182 --> 00:16:59,560
What do you plan to do now, Dr. Masumi?

251
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:00,811
I…

252
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:06,316
I want to uncover the truth
behind the Shiramine case

253
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,402
and clear Serizawa's name.

254
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:09,570
To do that,

255
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:14,658
I intend to find the real culprit
of the current serial killings.

256
00:17:16,076 --> 00:17:17,786
What do you mean by that?

257
00:17:19,246 --> 00:17:20,706
Supervisor.

258
00:17:20,789 --> 00:17:22,166
What brings you here?

259
00:17:22,249 --> 00:17:25,335
I just came to pack up my things
before our move-out.

260
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:29,798
I'm sorry. We were using this room
without permission.

261
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:30,883
Never mind that.

262
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:33,761
What do you mean by a wrongful conviction?

263
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:46,982
Sorry, I'm late.

264
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,818
Were you busy today?

265
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:50,819
Yes.

266
00:17:50,903 --> 00:17:54,823
After the autopsy, I had to take Haruto
to his cram school.

267
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:01,705
Kyoko.

268
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,292
I have a favor to ask.

269
00:18:09,004 --> 00:18:13,592
At the very bottom of my desk drawer,

270
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:17,096
there is an old envelope.

271
00:18:18,013 --> 00:18:19,264
Bring it to me.

272
00:18:20,307 --> 00:18:21,391
An envelope?

273
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:27,064
It's the forensic data
from the Shiramine case.

274
00:18:30,859 --> 00:18:32,569
What are you going to do with it?

275
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:36,949
I'm going to give it to Masumi.

276
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:42,496
Did Masumi put you up to this?

277
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:45,082
No.

278
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,334
This is my own choice.

279
00:18:48,669 --> 00:18:49,837
Why?

280
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:54,758
It's always about Masumi with you.

281
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:58,428
That's not true.

282
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:01,515
Think about Haruto.

283
00:19:01,598 --> 00:19:03,475
This is a critical time.

284
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:07,104
And besides,
that case is already over, isn't it?

285
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:11,692
We just concluded that it was.

286
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:18,448
I can't just die

287
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:22,578
leaving things like this.

288
00:19:37,426 --> 00:19:39,094
KYOKO KUJO

289
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:41,180
Hello?

290
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:43,599
<i>Masumi?</i>

291
00:19:43,682 --> 00:19:45,976
Kyoko. What's wrong?

292
00:19:46,852 --> 00:19:48,937
Sorry to call out of the blue.

293
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:50,939
Did something happen?

294
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:53,233
My father has a message for you.

295
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:56,820
It seems he has some data
he wants to hand over to you.

296
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:02,910
<i>Can you come pick them up</i>
<i>when you have time?</i>

297
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:04,328
I'll come tomorrow.

298
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,998
Tell the professor I'll come tomorrow.

299
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,168
All right.

300
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,255
Thanks for calling.

301
00:20:27,809 --> 00:20:30,103
SHIRAMINE SERIAL FEMICIDE CASE

302
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:37,486
MINISTRY OF HEALTH, LABOR AND WELFARE

303
00:20:40,614 --> 00:20:45,452
Are you trying to clear
a wrongful conviction all by yourself?

304
00:20:45,535 --> 00:20:48,747
I believe that's also why the MEJ

305
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:52,125
was suddenly shut down.

306
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:56,755
Kiryu, do you have a minute?

307
00:20:57,506 --> 00:20:58,423
Coming.

308
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,302
What is it?

309
00:21:02,386 --> 00:21:05,305
Since you've finally returned
to our department,

310
00:21:05,389 --> 00:21:07,349
I would like to ask you to handle this.

311
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:09,476
SUPPORT FOR YOUNG PEOPLE
EXPERIENCING FINANCIAL HARDSHIP

312
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:10,644
What?

313
00:21:10,727 --> 00:21:11,687
Isn't this…

314
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:15,274
It's the youth poverty support project
that you submitted before.

315
00:21:15,857 --> 00:21:19,528
But I thought someone else
was put in charge of this.

316
00:21:19,611 --> 00:21:22,572
At the time, I wanted you
to focus entirely on the MEJ,

317
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:24,825
but you are the right fit
for this after all.

318
00:21:28,328 --> 00:21:29,246
Thank you.

319
00:21:29,913 --> 00:21:30,831
Good luck.

320
00:21:30,914 --> 00:21:32,374
I'm expecting great things.

321
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:41,508
That's great.

322
00:21:41,591 --> 00:21:44,428
It's the project
you've wanted to handle for ages.

323
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:58,150
So, how is everyone's new workplace?

324
00:21:58,233 --> 00:21:59,568
Are you doing well?

325
00:21:59,651 --> 00:22:03,322
We have a full staff,
and it's actually not bad.

326
00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:07,576
To be honest, I've been able
to spend more time with my kid.

327
00:22:08,493 --> 00:22:10,912
They let me leave right on time every day.

328
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:11,997
Me too.

329
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:14,583
When they suddenly told us
we were closing,

330
00:22:14,666 --> 00:22:16,460
I wondered what would happen, but…

331
00:22:17,377 --> 00:22:21,631
It must have been really tough for
Ms. Kiryu to find new jobs for all of us.

332
00:22:21,715 --> 00:22:25,552
But don't you sort of miss
the vibe at the MEJ?

333
00:22:25,635 --> 00:22:28,096
I know, the adrenaline rush
from being so busy.

334
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:32,142
We even pulled all-nighters,
so at the time I just wanted a break,

335
00:22:32,768 --> 00:22:35,103
but I was gradually starting to enjoy it.

336
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:39,024
We were really starting
to come together as a team…

337
00:22:40,942 --> 00:22:44,529
But still, don't you think it's weird
for it to close down so abruptly?

338
00:22:44,613 --> 00:22:46,031
It is absolutely weird.

339
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:51,119
Well, the Ministry decided it,
so I guess there's nothing we can do.

340
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:52,037
Even so,

341
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:54,706
shutting it down after a few months
is strange for sure.

342
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:59,711
There must be some other reason behind it.

343
00:23:01,129 --> 00:23:02,214
Some other reason?

344
00:23:17,771 --> 00:23:18,688
Excuse me.

345
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:37,374
Masumi.

346
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:44,339
Where is Professor Kujo?

347
00:23:46,675 --> 00:23:48,635
His condition deteriorated overnight.

348
00:23:52,389 --> 00:23:53,807
He passed away this morning.

349
00:23:57,602 --> 00:24:00,230
The documents he wanted to give you…

350
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:03,859
I can't find where they are anymore.

351
00:24:05,443 --> 00:24:06,444
What?

352
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:10,198
I have to go now to handle the procedures.

353
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:16,788
Masumi.

354
00:24:21,376 --> 00:24:23,962
Please don't make my father
suffer any more than this.

355
00:24:56,745 --> 00:24:57,829
<i>Professor,</i>

356
00:24:57,913 --> 00:25:00,207
please tell me the truth!

357
00:25:12,552 --> 00:25:14,804
<i>A group supporting Shinichi Serizawa,</i>

358
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:18,683
<i>who received the death sentence</i>
<i>for the murder of three women</i>

359
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:21,811
<i>which happened in Shiramine 15 years ago,</i>

360
00:25:21,895 --> 00:25:24,731
<i>has started a petition drive,</i>
<i>claiming his innocence.</i>

361
00:25:24,814 --> 00:25:27,192
<i>My brother is no murderer!</i>

362
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:31,112
<i>Please lend us your support</i>
<i>so we can get a retrial!</i>

363
00:25:32,113 --> 00:25:37,619
<i>We are only demanding that the trial</i>
<i>be conducted fairly, a just trial.</i>

364
00:25:37,702 --> 00:25:40,789
Wow, she has really kept at it
for 15 years.

365
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:43,667
It's nearly impossible
to get a case reopened.

366
00:25:45,418 --> 00:25:46,586
Speaking of which,

367
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:50,465
I heard that the forensic pathologist,
Masahito Kujo, passed away.

368
00:25:51,466 --> 00:25:56,304
Then we don't have to worry about him
saying anything unnecessary anymore.

369
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:57,514
However,

370
00:25:57,597 --> 00:26:01,726
the family might still have the original
copies of the autopsy documents.

371
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:05,105
Just to be safe,

372
00:26:05,939 --> 00:26:08,149
make sure to stamp out
even the smallest spark.

373
00:26:10,026 --> 00:26:11,236
Understood.

374
00:26:15,699 --> 00:26:18,618
Are you making progress
in packing up the MEJ office?

375
00:26:18,702 --> 00:26:22,080
I'm sorry. There are return procedures
for the testing equipment,

376
00:26:22,163 --> 00:26:24,165
so could you give me a little more time?

377
00:26:24,249 --> 00:26:25,250
All right.

378
00:26:25,333 --> 00:26:26,668
I'll leave the rest to you.

379
00:26:26,751 --> 00:26:28,211
Please hurry, though.

380
00:26:28,295 --> 00:26:29,379
Understood.

381
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:35,635
Regarding the autopsy records
Professor Kujo owned,

382
00:26:35,719 --> 00:26:38,305
I wasn't able to receive them.

383
00:26:38,388 --> 00:26:39,264
I see.

384
00:26:39,347 --> 00:26:40,473
However,

385
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:45,562
while less definitive than that data,
there is one other lead.

386
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:51,693
The documents the prosecution
submitted during the trial back then

387
00:26:51,776 --> 00:26:56,197
include crime scene photos and other
materials that haven't been made public.

388
00:26:57,324 --> 00:27:00,118
The family requesting the retrial

389
00:27:00,201 --> 00:27:02,996
might have obtained them
through their lawyer.

390
00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:04,789
Yes.

391
00:27:04,873 --> 00:27:07,667
Shinichi Serizawa is innocent!

392
00:27:07,751 --> 00:27:10,170
Let's help save him!

393
00:27:10,754 --> 00:27:13,340
Shinichi Serizawa is innocent!

394
00:27:13,423 --> 00:27:15,050
Please.

395
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:16,843
Please.

396
00:27:16,926 --> 00:27:19,179
I want to prove my brother's innocence.

397
00:27:19,262 --> 00:27:20,889
Please help.

398
00:27:23,475 --> 00:27:24,893
Thank you very much.

399
00:27:47,540 --> 00:27:50,919
I apologize for dropping in on you
so suddenly.

400
00:27:52,587 --> 00:27:56,341
I had a few things
I wanted to say to you as well.

401
00:27:59,636 --> 00:28:01,137
For the past 15 years,

402
00:28:01,971 --> 00:28:06,893
I haven't forgotten your name
or Masahito Kujo's name even once.

403
00:28:08,812 --> 00:28:10,939
Because of your autopsy report,

404
00:28:11,564 --> 00:28:15,443
my brother was sentenced to death
for murders he didn't commit.

405
00:28:17,987 --> 00:28:18,947
How dare you

406
00:28:20,198 --> 00:28:21,950
show your face here after that?

407
00:28:28,998 --> 00:28:31,000
I am truly sorry for what happened.

408
00:28:33,711 --> 00:28:35,839
Do you think an apology makes it right?

409
00:28:36,965 --> 00:28:37,966
It was an irreparable--

410
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:40,301
Shinichi's life has been changed forever.

411
00:28:41,511 --> 00:28:42,470
Our parents

412
00:28:43,763 --> 00:28:48,685
passed away while desperately
proclaiming Shinichi's innocence.

413
00:28:50,019 --> 00:28:51,896
They felt nothing but regret.

414
00:28:55,024 --> 00:28:57,694
Because of your careless autopsy,

415
00:28:59,654 --> 00:29:02,407
our family's lives were completely ruined.

416
00:29:06,453 --> 00:29:08,079
What on earth

417
00:29:09,330 --> 00:29:11,124
do you want after all this time?

418
00:29:17,422 --> 00:29:19,758
The current serial murder case

419
00:29:21,176 --> 00:29:24,721
involving the deaths of six women

420
00:29:25,722 --> 00:29:29,768
might be the work of the real culprit
from the Shiramine incident.

421
00:29:32,312 --> 00:29:34,814
There's a possibility
that the real killer,

422
00:29:34,898 --> 00:29:36,483
who was never caught,

423
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:39,944
is committing murders again right now.

424
00:29:40,945 --> 00:29:42,989
If we find the real culprit,

425
00:29:43,072 --> 00:29:45,909
we can prove Shinichi's innocence.

426
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:49,829
To clear Shinichi's name
from this wrongful conviction,

427
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:52,499
won't you let me look into it once more?

428
00:29:52,582 --> 00:29:54,751
Why are you asking me?

429
00:29:55,543 --> 00:29:58,421
You should just ask the person
who performed the autopsy.

430
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:06,513
He passed away the other day.

431
00:30:08,973 --> 00:30:12,185
If you have the trial documents
from back then,

432
00:30:12,268 --> 00:30:14,187
would you please show them to me?

433
00:30:14,270 --> 00:30:15,897
Please, I beg you.

434
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:21,861
Do you think

435
00:30:23,029 --> 00:30:25,907
I could trust anything you say?

436
00:30:33,540 --> 00:30:36,793
Never show your face in front of me again.

437
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:38,586
Wait!

438
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:41,422
I want to clear Shinichi's name!

439
00:30:41,506 --> 00:30:43,883
Don't speak my brother's name so casually!

440
00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:53,601
For 15 years,
there hasn't been a single day

441
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:58,815
I haven't thought about
the Shiramine case either.

442
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:09,784
Please let me uncover the truth!

443
00:31:33,933 --> 00:31:35,143
Mama!

444
00:31:47,614 --> 00:31:49,407
Thank you very much.

445
00:31:51,618 --> 00:31:53,703
You're Kyoko Kujo, correct?

446
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:58,833
I'm Ota from the Tokyo District
Public Prosecutors Office.

447
00:32:00,126 --> 00:32:01,169
Here.

448
00:32:04,714 --> 00:32:08,176
My condolences regarding your father.

449
00:32:10,386 --> 00:32:12,639
Is this about the Shiramine case?

450
00:32:14,057 --> 00:32:15,934
Thank you for catching on so quickly.

451
00:32:16,601 --> 00:32:20,521
Could you hand over the autopsy documents
your father kept?

452
00:32:23,650 --> 00:32:25,151
There are no such documents.

453
00:32:27,403 --> 00:32:28,488
Excuse me.

454
00:32:30,114 --> 00:32:30,990
Haruto!

455
00:32:31,074 --> 00:32:32,200
Let's go.

456
00:32:35,703 --> 00:32:36,621
Did you have fun?

457
00:32:41,376 --> 00:32:43,878
<i>The investigation is progressing.</i>

458
00:32:44,379 --> 00:32:45,672
<i>Now, for the next story.</i>

459
00:32:46,172 --> 00:32:48,967
<i>Regarding a series of murders</i>
<i>targeting young women</i>

460
00:32:49,050 --> 00:32:51,219
<i>which are believed to be connected,</i>

461
00:32:51,302 --> 00:32:53,721
<i>we have interviewed</i>
<i>a family member of one victim.</i>

462
00:32:54,305 --> 00:32:57,392
<i>My wife died young.</i>

463
00:32:57,475 --> 00:32:58,685
YUKIE MORISHITA'S FATHER

464
00:32:58,768 --> 00:33:01,646
<i>I raised my daughter trying to make up</i>
<i>for her mother's absence.</i>

465
00:33:01,729 --> 00:33:03,022
<i>Why?</i>

466
00:33:03,106 --> 00:33:06,359
<i>Why did this have to happen</i>
<i>to my daughter?</i>

467
00:33:06,442 --> 00:33:08,945
<i>She didn't do anything wrong.</i>

468
00:33:09,737 --> 00:33:11,572
<i>I want Yukie back!</i>

469
00:33:12,573 --> 00:33:16,035
<i>Five other victims are believed</i>
<i>to be connected to this case.</i>

470
00:33:16,119 --> 00:33:18,955
<i>But there have currently</i>
<i>not been any arrests,</i>

471
00:33:19,038 --> 00:33:20,999
<i>and the investigators are at a loss.</i>

472
00:33:21,082 --> 00:33:23,042
<i>There's a possibility</i>
<i>that the real killer,</i>

473
00:33:23,126 --> 00:33:25,753
<i>who was never caught,</i>
<i>is committing murders again right now.</i>

474
00:33:25,837 --> 00:33:29,465
<i>Please let me uncover the truth!</i>

475
00:33:40,977 --> 00:33:46,774
I went to see Akiko,
Serizawa's older sister, but…

476
00:33:48,359 --> 00:33:50,236
she said she can't trust me

477
00:33:51,154 --> 00:33:52,947
and refused.

478
00:33:54,490 --> 00:33:55,491
I see.

479
00:33:56,075 --> 00:33:58,036
Professor Kujo and I…

480
00:33:59,871 --> 00:34:02,915
This is what we've done.

481
00:34:17,013 --> 00:34:18,056
What's this?

482
00:34:18,765 --> 00:34:22,310
Investigative materials
on the current serial murder case.

483
00:34:22,852 --> 00:34:24,937
I thought it might be of some reference.

484
00:34:26,189 --> 00:34:27,315
Are you sure?

485
00:34:27,398 --> 00:34:29,734
If I get caught, my head will roll.

486
00:34:30,777 --> 00:34:31,944
But with this,

487
00:34:32,862 --> 00:34:36,532
you might be able to find
the real killer, Dr. Masumi.

488
00:34:43,706 --> 00:34:45,208
Thank you very much.

489
00:34:48,419 --> 00:34:50,630
Six people have already been killed.

490
00:34:51,130 --> 00:34:53,758
If you include the Shiramine case,
it's nine people.

491
00:34:54,258 --> 00:34:55,551
Yukie!

492
00:34:56,135 --> 00:34:57,720
Yukie!

493
00:35:00,932 --> 00:35:04,060
I want to catch the culprit
no matter what.

494
00:35:05,895 --> 00:35:07,897
I will do whatever I can for that.

495
00:35:09,148 --> 00:35:10,274
I will also

496
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:12,735
give everything I have.

497
00:35:31,212 --> 00:35:32,588
SIXTH CASE INVESTIGATION PHOTOS

498
00:35:34,048 --> 00:35:36,551
MURDER OF A FEMALE
OFFICE WORKER IN MUSASHINO

499
00:35:48,354 --> 00:35:50,064
Packing up more things?

500
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:01,951
I myself

501
00:36:02,535 --> 00:36:04,412
don't even know

502
00:36:05,496 --> 00:36:07,373
what I'm trying to do.

503
00:36:11,043 --> 00:36:12,461
But I…

504
00:36:13,379 --> 00:36:15,631
don't want the MEJ to just disappear.

505
00:36:21,095 --> 00:36:22,722
I might be the only one

506
00:36:23,931 --> 00:36:25,516
who still has lingering regrets.

507
00:36:28,144 --> 00:36:30,271
It might be pointless in itself

508
00:36:31,939 --> 00:36:34,025
to worry so much.

509
00:36:37,695 --> 00:36:38,821
But…

510
00:36:40,656 --> 00:36:42,491
I just don't want to let it end here.

511
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:53,836
Please let me help with the investigation
of the Shiramine case too.

512
00:37:09,810 --> 00:37:11,145
Please do,

513
00:37:12,146 --> 00:37:13,231
Ms. Kiryu.

514
00:37:25,826 --> 00:37:27,828
I handed out flyers again yesterday,

515
00:37:27,912 --> 00:37:30,248
and a lot of people accepted them.

516
00:37:31,624 --> 00:37:34,335
Everyone is taking action
for you, Shinichi.

517
00:37:36,837 --> 00:37:37,964
Shinichi?

518
00:37:40,007 --> 00:37:41,050
Fifteen years…

519
00:37:43,261 --> 00:37:44,553
have passed.

520
00:37:51,018 --> 00:37:53,521
The next one to be executed might be me.

521
00:37:55,106 --> 00:37:57,316
I will never let that happen.
I'm going to--

522
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:59,151
You won't make it in time.

523
00:38:35,563 --> 00:38:37,148
Who might you be?

524
00:38:39,358 --> 00:38:40,985
I'm sorry for the sudden visit.

525
00:38:41,777 --> 00:38:42,820
I am Kiryu,

526
00:38:43,446 --> 00:38:47,241
the supervisor of Medical Examiner Japan.

527
00:38:47,325 --> 00:38:49,952
Could you please spare me
some time to talk?

528
00:38:55,416 --> 00:38:57,376
You've come all the way to my house.

529
00:38:57,460 --> 00:38:59,045
What are you planning?

530
00:39:02,048 --> 00:39:03,466
I am terribly sorry.

531
00:39:05,926 --> 00:39:09,513
But there is something
I want you to look at.

532
00:39:19,648 --> 00:39:20,649
What is this?

533
00:39:22,610 --> 00:39:24,528
These are the autopsy reports

534
00:39:24,612 --> 00:39:27,448
of all the bodies that Dr. Masumi
has dissected at MEJ.

535
00:39:28,699 --> 00:39:30,201
Why would you show me?

536
00:39:30,284 --> 00:39:32,536
I brought them on my own judgment.

537
00:39:34,330 --> 00:39:37,291
I wanted you to read them.

538
00:39:43,881 --> 00:39:48,469
Since MEJ was closed down
after just a few months,

539
00:39:49,345 --> 00:39:53,933
we didn't get to handle that many bodies.

540
00:39:54,725 --> 00:39:55,893
Still,

541
00:39:57,103 --> 00:40:03,359
Dr. Masumi has faced the life of each
and every deceased person earnestly.

542
00:40:05,027 --> 00:40:06,487
Thanks to that,

543
00:40:06,570 --> 00:40:09,824
the truth that had been overlooked
was brought to light.

544
00:40:11,784 --> 00:40:13,702
We were able to save the living,

545
00:40:14,620 --> 00:40:17,373
and also deliver the voices
of the deceased.

546
00:40:21,085 --> 00:40:22,670
Dr. Masumi…

547
00:40:24,839 --> 00:40:29,510
never let even the slightest thing amiss
go unnoticed.

548
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:35,599
He will always reveal the truth.

549
00:40:37,476 --> 00:40:38,644
Because

550
00:40:39,937 --> 00:40:41,814
he does it for the sake of the deceased,

551
00:40:44,358 --> 00:40:47,069
but also for the sake of those
who are alive.

552
00:41:04,503 --> 00:41:05,713
Welcome back.

553
00:41:06,297 --> 00:41:07,131
Thank you.

554
00:41:20,436 --> 00:41:24,732
I'm very sorry for making
a one-sided request the other day

555
00:41:25,232 --> 00:41:29,528
without considering your feelings.

556
00:41:35,534 --> 00:41:36,619
After you left,

557
00:41:37,870 --> 00:41:40,247
I thought about what you told me.

558
00:41:44,043 --> 00:41:45,961
In order to get a retrial,

559
00:41:46,462 --> 00:41:48,506
we need to find new evidence,

560
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:55,054
or otherwise prove that the evidence used
for the verdict was flawed.

561
00:41:58,807 --> 00:42:00,309
We have been searching

562
00:42:01,185 --> 00:42:05,022
for a forensic medicine doctor
who would redo the evaluation.

563
00:42:06,649 --> 00:42:07,483
However,

564
00:42:08,484 --> 00:42:10,611
no one would take the job.

565
00:42:11,654 --> 00:42:12,613
No one?

566
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:19,828
A re-evaluation is also an act of refuting
Professor Kujo's results.

567
00:42:20,746 --> 00:42:24,291
Since he was an authority
in the forensic medicine world…

568
00:42:25,668 --> 00:42:30,172
I think everyone had their hesitations
about taking it on.

569
00:42:32,258 --> 00:42:36,178
As well as that, demanding a retrial

570
00:42:36,804 --> 00:42:41,350
means objecting to the past judgment
of the prosecution.

571
00:42:43,018 --> 00:42:45,896
There wasn't a single doctor
who would go out of their way

572
00:42:45,980 --> 00:42:49,191
to take a request that would turn
the prosecution into an enemy.

573
00:42:59,034 --> 00:43:01,328
RESULTS OF INVESTIGATION

574
00:43:01,412 --> 00:43:03,539
These are the prosecution's materials

575
00:43:04,331 --> 00:43:07,001
which we obtained
through evidence disclosure.

576
00:43:11,922 --> 00:43:13,173
Mr. Mizusawa…

577
00:43:16,385 --> 00:43:17,678
I still

578
00:43:18,637 --> 00:43:20,556
cannot forgive you.

579
00:43:24,727 --> 00:43:27,187
But I will entrust you with this.

580
00:43:31,650 --> 00:43:34,820
Please prove that the autopsy results

581
00:43:35,946 --> 00:43:37,698
were fabricated.

582
00:43:44,997 --> 00:43:46,081
I promise

583
00:43:47,583 --> 00:43:49,793
I will reveal the truth.

584
00:44:07,519 --> 00:44:10,856
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.
